mrigger added on 2020-01-01 22:29:52:
Consider the following test case:
PRAGMA encoding = 'UTF16';
CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE vt0 USING fts5(c0);
INSERT INTO vt0 VALUES (SUBSTR(x'37', ''));
INSERT INTO vt0(vt0) VALUES('integrity-check'); -- database disk image is malformed
Unexpectedly, the integrity check fails with an error. This issue could be related to the open FTS4 bug [1dc432db3b].
